README The Dundee Treebank

You are allowed to use the work for research purposes.

The file TheDundeeTreebank_vx-x.csv contains manual dependency annotations described in:

Barrett, Agic and Søgaard (2015) "The Dundee Treebank" In: Proc. of the 14th International Workshop on Treebanks and 
Linguistic Theories (TLT14)

The file contains the following columns
Itemno,	WNUM, SentenceID, ID, CPOS, Head, DepRel

Itemno		contains the number of the article (1-20) of the Dundee corpus. 
WNUM		contains a word number that maps to the Dundee Corpus. The Dundee corpus has punctuation and contractions glued to the main word. For this version we separated them but kept the same WNUM for both parts
SentenceID	Unique SentenceID within the same Itemno.
ID 		Unique word ID within the same SentenceID. This column is referred to in the col DepRel
CPOS		Penn Treebank Part-of-speech
Head		The ID of the head of this word
DepRel		The type of dependency relation to the head

In case of questions, please contact barrett[at]hum.ku.dk